\begin_layout Standard
The paper considers a model where status amounts to a position maintained
 by the participant's social capital investments.
 It uses a decision theory framework for uncertainty inherent in status
 considerations and investigates the role of income gaps on expenditures
 that carry some status while also having an effect on the income mobility
 of the participants.
