\begin_layout Standard
The above model provides three important details pertaining to status-expenditur
es in an environment of income inequalities.
 First, there are only two long-term states of the poor-rich relationship
 that exist for status competitions under a diminishing wealth utility -
 one where both rich and poor participate in status competitions and another
 where only rich stand to benefit from status competitions.
 The particular detail demonstrates how income differences limit the benefit
 from status competitions to the poor - providing a quantitative basis for
 observations on social limits to growth in the literature 
